body.name: YEZriler (2-Pack) ATX CPU 8 Pin Male to PCIe 8 Pin (6+2) Male Power Adapter Sleeved Cable for Corsair Modular Power Supply 25-inch (63cm)
deliveryMessages: FREE delivery Saturday, February 17 on orders shipped by Amazon over $35
Or fastest delivery Friday, February 16. Order within 25 mins
features: CPU 8P - PCIe 8P(6+2): ATX 8 pin male end to plug into the power supply (NOTE: the 8 pin male connector is ATX 8 pin, not pci-e 8 pin.) and PCIe 8 pin(6+2) male end to plug into the video graphics card.(NOTE: the 8 pin end and 8 pin(6+2) male end cannot be used interchangeably);

Only designed for graphics vedio cards, it doesn't work with motherboards: Compatible with 6-pin & 8-pin graphics cards from regular manufacturers such as: ASUS/ASRock/Gigabyte/Radeon/Sapphire/NVIDIA Tesla/etc.(The 8 pin (6+2) ends could be used as 6 pin or 8 pin end by sliding on/off the 2 pin.);

Compatibility: Compatible with Corsair RM/RMX/RMi/HX/HXi/AX/AXi/SF/TX/TX-M/CS/CS-M/CX/CX-M series,Greatwall BTX-650SD/750SD/1000SD/EPS 1250DA/1560DA, Cougar CMX400W/450W/CX series/GX800W/GX600W/GX1050W,Antec Neo Eco 400M/650M/550M, Tt smart SE530/SE730, Thermaltake toughpower xt platinum 1275W/775W, OCZ 500M/700M XSP series, OCZ 700w mod x stream-pro;(NOTE: Do not work with AX1200.)

Parameter: Length(including connectors): 25-inch(63cm), Gauge: 1007-18AWG(standard tin-coating copper wire), Quantity: 2pcs, Hook loop strip*1pcs (only designed for graphics vedio cards, it will not work with motherboards);

Attention Please: This cable was only designed for the brand and model as listed in the 3rd Point.(Not compatible with EVGA and seasonic power supply.) If you use other incompatible brand PSUs or types, it will definitely burn or damage the PSUs or graphics cards. Please carefully check the compatible types or contact us if you are not sure if it supports your power supply;
body.description: Features: The YEZriler ATX 8 Pin male to PCIe 8 Pin (6+2) male cable is to provide a convenient solution for adding extra PCI Express connectors to your existing power supply; Support: Corsair RM/RMX/RMi/HX/HXi/AX/AXi/SF/TX/TX-M/CS/CS-M/CX/CX-M series all RM series/RM550x/RM650x/RM750x White/RM750x/RM850x White/RM850x/RM1000x/RM650i/RM750i/RM850i/RM1000i/HX750/HX850/HX1000/HX1200 /HX750i/HX850i/HX1000i/HX1200i/AX760i/AX860i/AX1200i/AX1500i Greatwall BTX-650SD/750SD/1000SD/EPS 1250DA/1560DA Cougar CMX400W/450W/CX series/GX800W/GX600W/GX1050W,Antec Neo Eco 400M/650M/550M Tt smart SE530/SE730, Thermaltake toughpower xt platinum 1275W/750W; OCZ 700M XSP series, OCZ 700w mod x stream-pro Spec: Length(including connectors): 25-inch(63cm) Connectors: 1x 8 pin (6+2) PCIe male, 1x ATX 8 pin male Gauge: 1007-18AWG(standard tin-coating copper wire) What You Get: ATX 8 Pin male to PCIe 8 Pin (6+2) male cable*2pcs; Hook loop strip*1pcs; Please Note: 1.Please check the specifications of your graphics card and PSU for power requirements when to use this cable. 2.This cable was only designed for graphics vedio cards, it does not work with motherboards;

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars RM850x and RTX 3080
reviews.reviewText: Like others, I was a little concerned with what the quality would be based on the price, but these are perfect for what I wanted. They match the Corsair braided/sleeved cables perfectly and seem to be of equal quality. No problems with my Corsair RM850 and an EVGA RTX 3080.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I got this for my Corsair power supply, works great and as intended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works with my AX860
reviews.reviewText: Was a bit hesitant to use with my Corsair AX860 since it’s possible to blow it up with cables that aren’t compatible, but it did work with my PSU as the description stated. No issues with it so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Didn't fit rm750x
reviews.reviewText: Bought this alongside a new GPU. When they came in, I couldn't connect them to the PSU due to two specific reasons1. piece of plastic connecting two of the top side pins on the PSU end (interestingly, this end fit into my GPU.)2. wrong pin housing shapes on PSU connection end.I even tried putting the PCIe end into the PSU, and while it fit somewhat, it wasn't enough to make a connection nor would have it be secure if it could.I also looked at the pictures of the PSU side connections posted in this listing, the cables I received WERE NOT THE SAME. Pictures are correct, but cables I have in my hand, aren't.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worked well with Rm750 and RTX 3080
reviews.reviewText: I was a little hesitant with how cheap these braided cables were. But they worked well and were short enough that I didn’t have to do much cable management. I would buy again

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2022
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on July 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: Incompatible for CPU Usage (in my experience)
reviews.reviewText: Item was packaged simply, with an additional velcro orange cable tidy.However, I ran these cables to my power supply and found that my computer would not boot. There was some signs of life, as the LED's on my RAM were lit but the fans etc but the motherboard would not go through the POST boot cycle.I replaced the cables with the originally supplied ones from Corsair and the PC booted fine. These may be compatible with a GPU, though I didn't try after my initial experience.Its worth noting that certain Corsair Power Supplies would not be compatible with these cables as they've started to implement a smaller plug on the power-supply side of the cable.
